ents, Mrs. Lopez displays the idolized Franklin enjoying Parisian life with his customary zest, helping to launch the potato, investigating Mesmer's doctrines, and protecting the city with lightning rods.Mrs. Lopez is assistant editor in charge of French material for the Papers of Benjamin Franklin at Yale University.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000z978311053801440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300157598?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300157598423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300157598/original  a978-3-11-053801-4  Yale University Press eBook-Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles